					<h2>Video Transcription</h2>
					<p>
Hi everyone. My name is Derek Johnson from Tatango.com. Well, most of our clients here at Tatango send messages from their computer and from the web interface at Tatango.com. There are some clients that maybe just aren't by their computer at the right time when they need to send a campaign out to their customers. So what we've developed here at Tatango is what I like to call text in. That allows you to use your own mobile phone and send a message via SMS to Tatango, and then we repackage that message and send it out to your customers almost instantaneously.
					</p>
					<p>
How does this work and how can you do it on your own account? Well, you have to go first into Account Settings, and you have to check off the little box that says "Mobile Enable." You have you put your phone number so we know not just anybody can text in to your account. Once you've done that though, it's very, very simple. 
					</p>
					<p>
Let's say you're taking the day off as a business owner and you're at the beach and you've got to send a message. Well, you grab your mobile phone, sort of like this one, and you text to the phone number 68398. That's Tatango short code. Then what you do in the message body, you start your message with the pound symbol, and then anything following the pound symbol will be sent to your customers.
					</p>
					<p>
Once you're done, "Show this text message for half-off pizza." It looks good. All you have to do is click Send, and within a couple of seconds, that will go to Tatango and then it will go back out to all your customers just as it would from the web interface.
					</p>
					<p>
Well, hopefully that helps you guys learn and understand how to do a text in from your own mobile phone.
